section.t:
Transfer codings (see ) are not defined for HTTP/3;
the Transfer-Encoding header field          MUST NOT
 be used.

ul.li:
The :authority pseudo-header field contains the host and port to connect to
(equivalent to the authority-form of the request-target of CONNECT requests;
see ).

figure.artwork:
Push Stream Header {
  Stream Type (i) = 0x01,
  Push ID (i),
}

HTTP/3 Frame Format {
  Type (i),
  Length (i),
  Frame Payload (..),
}

HEADERS Frame {
  Type (i) = 0x01,
  Length (i),
  Encoded Field Section (..),
}

CANCEL_PUSH Frame {
  Type (i) = 0x03,
  Length (i),
  Push ID (i),
}

Setting {
  Identifier (i),
  Value (i),
}

SETTINGS Frame {
  Type (i) = 0x04,
  Length (i),
  Setting (..) ...,
}

PUSH_PROMISE Frame {
  Type (i) = 0x05,
  Length (i),
  Push ID (i),
  Encoded Field Section (..),
}

GOAWAY Frame {
  Type (i) = 0x07,
  Length (i),
  Stream ID/Push ID (i),
}

MAX_PUSH_ID Frame {
  Type (i) = 0x0d,
  Length (i),
  Push ID (i),
}
